column20: The accessibility of the professor outside of class. Having a small classroom allowed interactions with the professor that were extremely useful.
I found the class really helpful for what is coming up in the degree and it really helped me
The length of the first 3 homeworks helped a lot as I used the  5 weeks to catch up on my other work.
Learning more about algorithms commonly found in the computer science field (ie real world exampes).
column21: Not rushing through the content so fast and to go deeper in some subjects.

column20: Prof. Coleman was always available to discuss homework or address any questions after class or during office hours.
column21: It would have been helpful if Prof. Coleman recorded his lectures for future reference.

column20: He knows what he is talking about
column21: I do not know what he is talking about, it is very hard to grasp a point because he needs to understand we don't know a lot about this topic

column20: I found the course workload to have been helpful, especially as I balanced other courses. We had few assignments but they were evenly spaced out and also allowed for group collaboration. In this way, I was able to balance the work with my groupmates.
column21: I think having more time to go over the topics would have been helpful especially on the more complicated concepts. I also think having better whiteboard markers would have been beneficial because I often found myself struggling to see the writing on the board.

column20: The homework was very well structured and they helped me learn a lot about the topics in the course. They were challenging but also very helpful in my learning process.
column21: This course would have been more effective with some more structured notes that I could look at regarding the material and not just pictures of the textbook.

column20: I really liked this course, it was probably my favorite this semester. The way we did notes was interactive and very easy to follow along with, and homeworks were challenging but great practice and I feel like I learned a lot. The professor was also available and took any questions during lectures

column21: a little more clarity on exam topics

The course could have been more effective if the professor had been easy to approach with extension requests rather, than immediately denying them. Although assignments were typically assigned one to two weeks in advance, the programming tasks were often very challenging. Balancing these assignments with other classes and unexpected responsibilities made it difficult to complete them on time without encountering issues.

In my case, scheduling conflicts prevented me from attending office hours consistently, further limiting my time to work on assignments. Despite explaining these challenges or unexpected circumstances, the professor maintained a strict no-extension policy. However, sometimes all that was needed to successfully complete the work was an extra day or even just a few additional hours.

While I understand that adhering to deadlines is important, giving students some flexibility might really allow them to learn more and complete assignments without stressing over due dates. This way, they will be able to thoroughly grasp the material rather than rush through, thereby misunderstanding or incorrectly applying key concepts.
The HW was extremely difficult, I had much trouble comprehending the instructions most of the time.
